# Knuckle Joint Assembly (Reverse Engineered)

## Objective
Recreate a knuckle joint assembly in CAD based on standard reference geometry to understand its construction and working.

## Source
Geometry inspired from standard machine design references and publicly available diagrams.

## Components
- Eye end
- Fork end
- Knuckle pin
- Collar
- Taper pin

## What I Focused On
- Accurate part relationships and assembly constraints
- Understanding load transfer through the joint
- Modeling realistic clearances for motion

## Tools Used
- Fusion 360

## Learning Outcomes
- Gained understanding of joint mechanics and degrees of freedom
- Learned how to convert 2D reference geometry into 3D CAD models
- Practiced assembly constraints and component interfacing

## Future Work
- Perform design calculations for pin diameter based on load
- Validate using FEA
